{{ThisDateInRecentYears}}
{{Day}}

==Events==
* [[109]] &amp;ndash; Roman emperor [[Trajan]] inaugurates the [[Aqua Traiana]], an  [[Roman aqueduct|aqueduct]] that channels water from [[Lake Bracciano]], {{convert|40|km|mi|abbr=off}} north-west of [[Ancient Rome|Rome]].
* [[474]] &amp;ndash; [[Julius Nepos]] forces Roman usurper [[Glycerius]] to abdicate the [[throne]] and proclaims himself Emperor of the [[Western Roman Empire]].
* [[637]] &amp;ndash; The [[Battle of Moira]] is fought between the [[High King of Ireland]] and the Kings of [[Ulster]] and [[Dalriada]]. It is claimed to be largest battle in the history of [[Ireland]].
* [[972]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Cedynia]], the first documented victory of [[Poland|Polish]] forces, takes place.
*[[1128]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of São Mamede]], near [[Guimarães]]: forces led by [[Alfonso I of Portugal|Alfonso I]] defeat forces led by his mother [[Theresa, Countess of Portugal|Teresa of León]] and her lover [[Fernando Pérez de Traba]]. After this battle, the future king calls himself &quot;Prince of Portugal&quot;, the first step towards &quot;official independence&quot; that will be reached in [[1139]] after the [[Battle of Ourique]].
*[[1314]] &amp;ndash; [[First War of Scottish Independence]]: the [[Battle of Bannockburn]] concludes with a decisive victory by  [[Scottish people|Scottish]] forces led by [[Robert the Bruce]], though [[Kingdom of England|England]] did not recognize [[Kingdom of Scotland|Scottish]] independence until [[1328]] with the signing of the [[Treaty of Edinburgh-Northampton]].
*[[1340]] &amp;ndash; [[Hundred Years' War]]: [[Battle of Sluys]] &amp;ndash; The [[France|French]] fleet is almost destroyed by the English Fleet commanded in person by King [[Edward III of England|Edward III]].
*[[1374]] &amp;ndash; A sudden outbreak of [[Dancing mania|St. John's Dance]] causes people in the streets of [[Aachen]], [[Germany]], to experience [[hallucination]]s and begin to jump and twitch uncontrollably until they collapse from exhaustion.
*[[1497]] &amp;ndash; [[John Cabot]] lands in [[North America]] at [[Newfoundland (island)|Newfoundland]] leading the first European exploration of the region since the [[Vikings]].
*[[1509]] &amp;ndash; [[Henry VIII of England|Henry VIII]] and [[Catherine of Aragon]] are crowned King and Queen of England.
*[[1535]] &amp;ndash; The [[Anabaptist]] state of [[Münster Rebellion|Münster]] is conquered and disbanded.
*[[1571]] &amp;ndash; [[Miguel Lopez de Legazpi]] founds [[Manila]], the capital of the [[Republic of the Philippines]].
*[[1597]] &amp;ndash; The first [[Netherland|Dutch]] voyage to the [[East Indies]] reaches [[Bantam (city)|Bantam]] (on [[Java (island)|Java]]).
*[[1604]] &amp;ndash; [[Samuel de Champlain]] discovers the mouth of the [[Saint John River (New Brunswick)|Saint John River]], site of [[Reversing Falls]] and the present day city of [[Saint John, New Brunswick]], [[Canada]].
*[[1622]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Macau]]: The Dutch attempt but fail to capture [[Macau]].
*[[1717]] &amp;ndash; The [[Premier Grand Lodge of England]], the first [[Freemasonry|Masonic]] Grand Lodge in the world (now the [[United Grand Lodge of England]]), is founded in [[London]], [[England]].
*[[1779]] &amp;ndash; [[American Revolutionary War]]: The [[Great Siege of Gibraltar]] begins.
*[[1793]] &amp;ndash; The [[French Constitution of 1793|first Republican constitution]] in [[France]] is adopted.
*[[1812]] &amp;ndash; [[Napoleonic Wars]]: [[Napoleon I of France|Napoleon's]] [[La Grande Armée|Grande Armée]] crosses the [[Neman River]] beginning the [[Napoleon's Invasion of Russia|invasion]] of [[Russia]].
*[[1813]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Beaver Dams]]: a [[United Kingdom|British]] and Indian combined force defeats the [[United States Army]].
*[[1821]] &amp;ndash; The [[Battle of Carabobo]] takes place. It is the decisive battle in the war of independence of [[Venezuela]] from [[Spain]].
*[[1859]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Solferino]] (Battle of the Three Sovereigns): [[Sardinia]] and France defeat [[Austria]] in [[Solferino]], northern [[Italy]].
*[[1866]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Custoza (1866)|Battle of Custoza]]: an [[Austrian Empire|Austrian]] army defeats the [[Italy|Italian]] army during the [[Austro-Prussian War]].
*[[1880]] &amp;ndash; First performance of ''[[O Canada]]'', the song that would become the [[national anthem]] of [[Canada]], at the Congrès national des Canadiens-Français.
*[[1894]] &amp;ndash; [[Marie Francois Sadi Carnot]] is assassinated by [[Sante Geronimo Caserio]].
*[[1902]] &amp;ndash; King [[Edward VII of the United Kingdom]] develops [[appendicitis]], delaying his coronation.
*[[1913]] &amp;ndash; [[Greece]] and [[Serbia]] annul their alliance with [[Bulgaria]].
*[[1916]] &amp;ndash; [[Mary Pickford]] becomes the first female film star to sign a million dollar [[contract]].
*  1916   &amp;ndash; [[World War I]]: the [[Battle of the Somme]] begins with a week-long artillery bombardment on the [[Germany|German Line]].
*[[1918]] &amp;ndash; First [[airmail]] service in [[Canada]] from [[Montreal]] to [[Toronto]].
*[[1932]] &amp;ndash; A bloodless [[Siamese Revolution of 1932|Revolution]] instigated by the [[Khana Ratsadon|People's Party]] ends the absolute power of King [[Prajadhipok]] of [[Rattanakosin Kingdom|Siam]] (now [[Thailand]]).
*[[1938]] &amp;ndash; Pieces of a [[meteor]], estimated to have weighed 450 [[metric ton]]s when it hit the Earth's atmosphere and exploded, land near [[Chicora, Pennsylvania]].
*[[1939]] &amp;ndash; Siam is renamed [[Thailand]] by [[Plaek Pibulsonggram]], the country's third [[prime minister]].
*[[1947]] &amp;ndash; [[Kenneth Arnold]] makes the first widely reported [[Kenneth Arnold Unidentified Flying Object Sighting|UFO sighting]] near [[Mount Rainier]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]].
*[[1948]] &amp;ndash; Start of the [[Berlin Blockade]]: the [[Soviet Union]] makes overland travel between [[West Germany]] and [[West Berlin]] impossible.
*[[1949]] &amp;ndash; The first [[Westerns on television|television western]], ''[[Hopalong Cassidy]]'', is aired on [[NBC]] starring [[William Boyd (actor)|William Boyd]].
*[[1957]] &amp;ndash; In [[Roth v. United States]], the [[Supreme Court of the United States|U.S. Supreme Court]] rules that obscenity is not protected by the [[First Amendment to the United States Constitution|First Amendment]].
*[[1963]] &amp;ndash; The United Kingdom grants [[Zanzibar]] internal self-government.
*[[1981]] &amp;ndash; The [[Humber Bridge]] is opened to traffic, connecting [[Yorkshire]] and [[Lincolnshire]]. It would be the world's longest single-span suspension bridge for 17 years.
*[[1982]] &amp;ndash; &quot;The Jakarta Incident&quot;: [[British Airways Flight 9]] flies into a cloud of volcanic ash thrown up by the eruption of [[Mount Galunggung]], resulting in the failure of all four engines.
*[[1985]] &amp;ndash; [[STS-51-G]] [[Space Shuttle Discovery]] completes its mission, best remembered for having [[Sultan bin Salman bin Abdulaziz Al Saud]], the first [[Arab]] and first [[Muslim]] in space, as a [[Payload Specialist]].
*[[2002]] &amp;ndash; The [[Igandu train disaster]] in [[Tanzania]] kills 281, the worst train accident in [[Africa]]n history.
*[[2004]] &amp;ndash; In New York, [[capital punishment]] is declared unconstitutional.
*[[2010]] &amp;ndash; [[John Isner]] of the [[United States]] defeats [[Nicolas Mahut]] of [[France]] at [[Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon]], in [[Isner–Mahut match at the 2010 Wimbledon Championships|the longest match in professional tennis history]].
*[[2012]] &amp;ndash; The last known individual of [[Chelonoidis nigra abingdonii]], a subspecies of the [[Galápagos tortoise]], dies, making the species extinct.

