* [[Battle of Bannockburn|Bannockburn Day]] ([[Scotland]])
* [[Battle of Carabobo|Battle of Carabobo Day]] ([[Venezuela]])
* Christian [[Feast Day]]:
** [[Nativity of St. John the Baptist]]
** [[June 24 (Eastern Orthodox liturgics)]]

* [[Caboclo|Day of the Caboclo]] ([[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas State]], [[Brazil]])
* [[Discovery Day]], observed on the nearest Monday ([[Newfoundland and Labrador]])
* Earliest day on which [[Mother's Day]] can fall, while June 30 is the latest; celebrated on the last Sunday in June. ([[Kenya]])
* [[Bahá'í calendar|Feast of Raḥmat]] ([[Bahá'í Faith]])
* [[Inti Raymi]], a [[winter solstice]] festival and a [[New Year]] in the [[Andes]] of the Southern Hemisphere ([[Sacsayhuamán]])
* [[Midsummer Day|St John's Day]] and the second day of the [[Midsummer|Midsummer celebrations]] (although this is not the astronomical summer solstice, see [[June 20]]) ([[Roman Catholic Church]], [[Northern Europe]]), and its related observances: 
** [[St John's Day (Estonia)|Jaanipäev]] ([[Estonia]])
** [[Jāņi]] ([[Latvia]])
** [[Midsummer|Midsummer Day]] ([[England]])
** [[National Holiday (Quebec)]] 
** [[Saint Jonas' Festival]] or ''Joninės'' ([[Lithuania]])
** [[Sânziene]] (western [[Carpathian Mountains]] of [[Romania]])
** [[Fors Fortuna]] ([[Roman Empire]])

